In terms of technology segmentation, the probe card market differentiates between advanced probe cards and standard probe cards. Advanced probe cards integrate cutting-edge technologies such as microfabrication techniques and advanced materials to elevate testing capabilities, enabling semiconductor manufacturers to conduct more sophisticated and precise testing procedures. Standard probe cards, although more conventional in design, continue to serve as reliable solutions for routine testing applications within the semiconductor industry, providing consistent performance and efficiency for testing various semiconductor devices.

The application-based segmentation of the probe card market includes DRAM, flash memory, and logic devices. DRAM probe cards are crucial for testing memory devices, ensuring their functionality and performance meet industry standards. Flash memory probe cards are specifically designed to test non-volatile memory chips, playing a vital role in ensuring the reliability and efficiency of these storage solutions. Logic device probe cards focus on testing integrated circuits that perform logical operations in electronic devices, emphasizing the importance of accurate and comprehensive testing to maintain product quality and functionality.

